# Frontend (React + Vite)

## Preserve

- Current visual style, layout, sidebar, Russian copy.
- Inline/CSS patterns already used in `src/` (no full redesign).

## Data and IDs

- Use entity `id` from API responses for PATCH/DELETE paths.
- Never hardcode demo IDs in write flows.
- Refresh list/detail state after successful create/update/delete.

## Errors and feedback

- Show visible validation (form errors, toasts).
- Do not silently swallow API 422/404/500.
- `requestWithMockFallback` must not hide failures when API is configured.

## Responsive

- Keep mobile/tablet layouts usable (`useMediaQuery`, existing CSS).
- No severe horizontal overflow on forms/modals/tables.

## Verify

```bash
npm run build
```

Run `npm run lint` when touching ESLint-covered files.
